PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775347371
OL,3,CMisogyny among pupils a 'ticking time
OL,4,Cbomb' in UK schools, warns union
OL,6,FAnna Edmundson, director of policy and
OL,7,Fsocial change at the NSPCC, said it
OL,8,Fwas "disheartening" to hear misogyny
OL,9,Fis becoming more commonplace in
OL,10,Fschools.
OL,12,FShe added that as well as girls being
OL,13,Faffected, boys are telling NSPCC "they
OL,14,Fdon't want to express these views but
OL,15,Ffeel pressure from peers to do so",
OL,16,Fstating that they need guidance and
OL,17,Fhelp from safe adults at home, schools
OL,18,Fand the community.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
